:"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25435,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/20\/my-wife-aisha-invited-too\/","url_meta":{"origin":13723,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Marriage: Is my wife Aisha invited to dinner, too?","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 20, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, had a Persian neighbour who would make good soup. He made some for the Prophet and then came to invite him. The Prophet said, \u201cAnd this is my wife, Aisha.\u201d The man said no, so the Prophet said\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26698,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/07\/03\/janazah-stand-or-sit\/","url_meta":{"origin":13723,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Janazah: Better to stand for funerals, permissible to sit","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 3, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Ali reported: We saw the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, stand for funerals and so we stood up. The Prophet would sit and so we sat. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 962 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim Al-Nawawi said, \u201cThe preferred opinion of Al-Mutawalli among our scholars is that\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26770,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/08\/26\/makruh-partial-shave-head\/","url_meta":{"origin":13723,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Hair: Discouragement to partially shave head, leave rest","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 26, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, prohibited partial shaving. It was said to Nafi\u2019, \u201cWhat is partial shaving?\u201d Nafi\u2019 said, \u201cIt is to shave part of a boy\u2019s head and leave the rest.\u201d In another narration, the Prophet said, \"Shave it all or\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":29323,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/13\/prophet-not-urinate-standing\/","url_meta":{"origin":13723,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Cleanliness: The Prophet does not urinate standing up","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 13, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would not urinate unless he was sitting. Al-Tirmidhi said, \u201cThe prohibition of urinating while standing means it is a matter of etiquette and not absolute forbiddance.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 12 Grade: Jayyid (very good) according to Al-Nawawi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":13795,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/04\/28\/hamd-eating-drinking\/","url_meta":{"origin":13723,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Gratitude: Praise Allah for food and drink","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 28, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, Allah is pleased with a servant who praises Him when he eats, or praises Him when he drinks.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2734 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13723","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=13723"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13723\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=13723"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=13723"},{"taxonomy":"pos